# Skyview XC Team Website - AI Development Rules

## Project Context
You are working on a static website for a high school cross country team. The site is hosted on AWS S3 with CloudFront CDN and focuses on distributing weekly newsletters and training resources.

## Code Style Rules

### HTML
- Use semantic HTML5 elements
- Include descriptive comments for major sections
- Keep all styles inline (no external CSS files)
- Mobile-responsive design is required

### File Structure
- New newsletters go in `newsletters/` folder
- Name format: `week#-newsletter.html`
- New resources go in root directory
- Always include back navigation to index.html

### Color Scheme
- Primary: #667eea
- Secondary: #764ba2
- Info boxes: #f8f9fa, #fff3cd, #d1ecf1
- Success: #28a745
- Warning: #ffc107
- Danger: #dc3545

## AWS Deployment
- Test locally first: `python3 -m http.server 8000`
- Deploy with: `npm run deploy-s3`
- CloudFront cache takes 5-15 min to update

## Content Guidelines
- Maintain encouraging, supportive tone
- Follow Jack Daniels training methodology
- Provide both Varsity and JV workout options
- Target audience: high school athletes and parents

## When Adding Features
1. Check CLAUDE.md for detailed instructions
2. Test all links before deploying
3. Ensure mobile responsiveness
4. Keep AWS costs minimal (currently ~$0.10/month)

## Important Files
- CLAUDE.md - Detailed AI instructions
- README.md - User documentation
- scripts/deploy-s3.sh - Deployment script
- .env.example - Environment variables template